The paper discusses the behavior of networked systems, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on coordinated behavior and output responses suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The use of random transfer functions and probability theory also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The discussion of model reduction and robustness suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
